About

  A command line utility that reloads the active tab in chrome(*) when it is
  invoked.

  (*) patches for other browsers welcome


Usage

  Open chrome. Run the `reload-browser` executable.
  
  Pairs well with `wach` - https://github.com/quackingduck/wach
  
    wach "make article.html && reload-browser"

Stability

  This program should be considered "alpha". It works on the author's machine
  but needs more testing in the wild. Bug reports welcome.

Installation

  Install the chrome extension:
  https://github.com/downloads/quackingduck/reload-browser/reload-browser-v0.1.0.crx

  Install the command with npm:
    
    npm install -g reload-browser
